    h2.
      What is binge eating disorder (BED)?

    p.
      Binge eating disorder, now a distinct diagnosis in #[em DSM-5]#[sup Â®], is characterized by#[sup 1]:

    ul.bullet
      li.
        Recurring episodes (at least #[br.hide--desktop]once weekly for 3 months) of consuming an abnormally large amount of food in a short period of time (eg, within 2 hours), compared with others
      li.
        Experiencing a lack of control over eating during an episode
      li.
        Significant distress regarding binge eating

    p.
      During a binge, adults with BED may consume food faster than normal, when not hungry, until uncomfortably full. They may also consume food alone due to embarrassment, and may feel disgusted, depressed, or guilty after bingeing.

